<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="pvm_exit">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>pvm_exit</refname>
    <refpurpose> tells the local pvmd that this process is leaving PVM.  </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>[info] = pvm_exit()</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>info</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>integer</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><literal>pvm_exit</literal> tells the local pvmd
    that this process is leaving PVM.
    This routine does not kill the process, which can continue to
    perform tasks just like any other serial process.</para>
    <para><literal>pvm_exit</literal> should be called by all PVM processes before
    they stop or exit for good. It <literal>must</literal> be called
    by processes that were not started with <literal>pvm_spawn</literal>.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[ 
pvm_exit()
 ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
  <refsection role="see also">
    <title>See Also</title>
    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member>
        <link linkend="pvm">pvm</link>
      </member>
    </simplelist>
  </refsection>
</refentry>
